I appreciate all your feed back yesterday on what it is you want to see from me! And almost all of you said you wanted me to post lessons! So here y’all go! This is a quick lick I use for hits on the + of 2 and the + of 4 mainly.  Very useful and I thought you’d all be able to apply this to your own playing pretty easily! Enjoy 😏. If you want to make it even hipper, take the main pattern (RLLKLKK) and put that group of 7 over 16th notes and 16th note triplets 😏. I can post about that take on it later 😘. Thanks for all the support!

#timstranscriptions day 71: GROOVE. It has always blown me away how Benny can play such technically impressive drum-nerd stuff but also has the ability and musicality to just lay down an insanely groovy vibe with GREAT drum tones. There are so few drummers that can operate at both ends of the spectrum. Benny Greb is absolutely one of them. Who's your favorite drummer that grooves and shreds equally well?

YouTube video just went live where I’m breaking down why I love this clip of Tony’s playing so much. Thanks so much to @saschasalles for tagging me in this and challenging me to transcribe it. You can download the sheet music and watch the full breakdown video from the link in my bio.

a short little lick for you to spice up your fills and grooves! it’s starts on beat 3 with two ghosted grace notes on the snare - as always 3 tempos and some applications and variations in a groove context, try moving this pattern around on the kit as well! give it a try and tag me!

last week i posted a lick in my story and asked you if it was in 6 or 9. some of you told me to make a breakdown so here it is! it’s a short group of 9 notes (as you can see in the brackets below the sticking) in sextuplets that repeats once and ends with a group of 6 to fit in one bar. this works great in a solo or a jam but please don’t play this at gigs haha.. of course you can just take the pattern of 9, repeat it longer, flip it around, displace it or just try different orchestrations or accents, just be creative with it. give it a try!
